how do you cure laziness has anyone turned the corner on this one and begun a new life of physical activity and general housekeeping how did you do it first of all find a physical activity you enjoy stretch your horizon it doesn't have to be just sports i like rock climbing start slowly then increase the amount of time you spend doing this thing everyday if you're into pets get a dog and go to a pet friendly trail and take a walk play music while you do chores to encourage yourself listen to a talk show or a book on tape or if you have just one room to clean up while a favorite tv program of yours is on watch the show but during the commercials run around cleaning up as fast as you can Garfield Shaggy dog story Dog agility Maison Ikkoku Drag racing Peter Griffin MTV Social rule Kender Surveillance Domestic rabbit Sport Friends W.I.T.C.H. Dog training Milton H. Erickson The Brady Bunch Synthesizer MTV2 Taikyoku shogi Fancy rat Spidey Super Stories Human sexual behavior Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Pop punk Gothic rock Music genre Australian Broadcasting Corporation Professional wrestling slang The Price Is Right Bicycle Glossary of climbing terms The Star Wars Holiday Special The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Guadalupe Mountains National Park Bubble Bobble Beavis and Butt-head Teacher's Pet (Disney) Iditarod Nuclear power Hamster The Joker's Wild Hearing impairment Sumo RISC The Doctor Dances Upholstery Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Prostate cancer Joni Mitchell Mixed-breed dog Good Times "Weird Al" Yankovic Hiking Black hole Long Path Kodocha Escape from New York Tony Bennett Alcoholics Anonymous The Time Machine Ben Johnson (athlete) Random walk Floppy disk The Ventures Table tennis The Smoking Room Mixtape Television in the United States Sonic the Hedgehog Marching band Family Guy Boards of Canada Sant Thakar Singh GunBound The Death Gate Cycle Sex and the City RuneScape quests Viterbi algorithm Leisure Animal r